is throne, sighing deeply.  His fingers tapping on the arm of his throne.  A spirit walks up to him::<br>
<br>
&quot;My Lord, everything is prepared.  Persephone should arrive at any moment.  Do you wish someone to greet her or...&quot;<br>
<br>
::With that Hades stood and waved his hand, silencing the spirit.  He started walking towards the doorway and exits the throne room.  He stood at the front of his palace awaiting her arrival::<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A> at: 10/2/01 8:02:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/2/01 8:35:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Queen's Arrival</span><hr size=1> ::a herald makes his strong but depressing noise. A few gaurds walk toward the palace with Persephone in the middle in a black and gold carrier with black see-through curtains carried by four 6'5 tall men . Her thick,brownish-black hair is hanging down perfectly straight, not a strand out of place. She wears a dark violet silk toga with golden trimmings and a dark purple diamond and gold necklace. Over her head is a black see through veil with violet and gold trimmings and a velvet onyx cloak with the hood down. her make-up is black, dark purple and violet, and completely flawless, making her light electric blue eyes looking icy. Despite her lovely face, she blots away the moisture from the rivers of tears she had shed earlier with Zeus and her mother.<br>
<br>
::when they are about 15 feet from Hades, they put the carrier down gently and the royal head gaurd walks to her from Hades, bows and holds her hand delicately as she takes his and steps out. The royal gaurd escorts her regally to Hades and bows and steps to the side and turns facing Hades' left. Persephone lowers her head and bows to the ground and slowly rises, keeping her head down:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/2/01 8:55:25 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Queen's Arrival</span><hr size=1> ::Hades bows his head slightly to his queen before extending his hand, to accept her into his Palace again.  He places her hand into his and bid her to rise.  His eyes and face solemn before all present.  The then turned with Persephone and walked her into the Palace.  Once the presence of all servants vanished, Hades smiled.  A smile of happiness for the first time in a long time.  Though he didn't show it most of the time, he did miss his bride.  He escorted her to the throne room before whispering into her ear::<br>
<br>
&quot;Shall I escort you to your throne, or to your bedchambers, or perhaps your private garden?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/2/01 9:00:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Queen's Arrival</span><hr size=1> ::looks up at him, her voice is more solem and humble than usual. But her eyes reveil her fragile innocence:: I have a throne? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/2/01 9:10:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Queen's Arrival</span><hr size=1> ::He turns and looks deep into here eyes, his head nodding:: &quot;Of course you have a throne, right beside mine.  It has always been there.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/2/01 9:25:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mixed Emotions</span><hr size=1> ::looks the other way sudden't feeling extremely stupid for such a dumb quesion. Thinks about not being in the Upperworld and missing her mother and brother so much. Automatically breaks into tears and flees away dpwn the hall past confused servants to her private garden::<br>
<br>
::A soon as she gets there, she sits on the edge of the large crystal pond. Sits on her knees looking down at her reflection, and keeps staring at it as it calms her nerves:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/3/01 1:11:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mixed Emotions 2</span><hr size=1> ::sits herself Indian style and begins to pick a flower's pettals shedding lightly silent tears, as she usually does when she returns the the place she hates most.  Lays herself down on a soft colorful flower bed and gently cries herself to sleep:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/3/01 1:24:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mixed Emotions 2</span><hr size=1> ::Hades walks out to her garden and stands just on the inside of it, watching Persephone.  He watches her sleep for quite sometime, hoping one day she will adjust to this place.  He sighs deeply as he waves his hand and summons two spirit servants.  Without saying a single thing they leave and return momentarily with a blanket which they lay over Persephone.  Hades watches her for a few moments more before going inside and sitting upon his throne again:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A> at: 10/3/01 1:27:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/3/01 6:52:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mixed Emotions 2</span><hr size=1> black sulfer circles above where persephone is sleeping out in the garden then forming under persephone's head sits Hecate with the young goddess's head cradled in her lap as she runs her pale skinny ebony fingers through Persephones dark hair. Sprinkling dark powder over her head she puts her in a peaceful sleep, the powder meant to scare nightmares away.<br>
moving from side to side she grined happy to have Persephone back. <p>*~`~* Hecate goddess of Sorcery, Silver-footed Queen of the Night *~`~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/3/01 8:59:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Awakened</span><hr size=1> ::after a long while, Persephone awakens to see Hectate and smiles softly for the first time since she's been back:: <br>
<br>
Why if it isn't mighty Hectate ::Sits up and leans over hugging her good and warmly:: I've missed you so much. Don't tell anyone I said this but....while I was in the realm of the living....me and Hades, for the very first time had... ::leans over whispering into her ear, then leans back as she finishes and smiles shyly as a rosy blush kisses her cheeks:: <br>
<br>
So being in the realm of the living made me miss him so much. I feel bad too since I ran off the way I did when I came back. I just had a cauldron of mixed emotions in me and I'm afraid I hurt his feelings. I'm going to go to him and apologize to him right now ::stands and takes Hectate's hand and helps her stand. Holds her elbow gently and leaves the garden and begins walking towards the throne room:: Come with me and tell me of your days here while I was away... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/4/01 6:54:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awakened</span><hr size=1> gets up with Persephone and walks along with her, as her black dress with silver stars sways softly against the ground <br>
<br>
&quot;i missed you too and as for my days here they went as uaual..spell casting and dwelling in hidden caves as for Hades...i'm sure he dosent mind that you ran of like that and i know he'll understand&quot;<br>
walks along with her to Hades throne. <p>*~`~* Hecate goddess of Sorcery, Silver-footed Queen of the Night *~`~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/4/01 8:21:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Forgiveness</span><hr size=1> ::walks into Hades' throne room and looks to hectate smling briefly before walking to his throne. Kneel to the ground until her hands and head are at level with his feet. Stays there as she speaks::<br>
<br>
Greeting your lordship. Please forgive me for leaving you so abruptly and rudely. i know I am not used to living to this place as i should be,  I did not mean to be so insolent. Will your highness bestow mercy upon me, please? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/7/01 10:55:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forgiveness</span><hr size=1> ::sighs after a long moment of silence and slowly rises and turns to leave the throne room with her regal head down and sad:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/8/01 5:30:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forgiveness</span><hr size=1> ::Hades sat in silence for a moment.  As she turned away, he cleared his throat and spoke::  &quot;My dear wife, there is really no need to be so formal with me.  In your case.  Though I am Lord of this Realm, you are still its Queen.  You and you alone may honor me as your husband, not necessarily as your Lord.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then sat back in his throne and patted the arm of her throne, motioning for her to take her seat beside him:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/8/01 6:10:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Forgiveness</span><hr size=1> ::smiles and crosses her arms defiantly:: I'm not sitting down in in that throne for one moment. I've been here for 8 hours and you haven't even given me at least one hug and kiss. And I know you have this huge, dark reputation, but we're alone so now you have no excuse.<br>
<br>
::taps her foot with a smart-allic look upon her face:: Well, what's it going to be? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/9/01 12:50:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awaiting Persephone</span><hr size=1> ::A plain smile crossed Hades' face.  He then non-chelantly pointed to Hecate:: &quot;Persephone, did you forget about the presense of our dear friend Hecate?&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then patted his lap indicating her to come sit down on his lap:: &quot;You could always sit here if you find your throne not to your satisfaction&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/9/01 9:14:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awaiting Persephone</span><hr size=1> ::turns to hectate and smiles motioning her to leave and winks. Walks over to him and sits on his lap with one arm wrapped aound his chest and over his shoulder. The other one around his back waist. Lays her head on his chest:: Did you miss me my love?<br>
<br>
Or has someone else kept your bed warm for me? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uvvvthegoddesshecatevvv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VVV The Goddess Hecate VVV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/9/01 5:15:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Awaiting Persephone</span><hr size=1> looking at the two of them she bows her head in respect to both of them and dissappears in a thick black cloud of sulfer to the desolute caves of the mortal realm <p>*~`~* Hecate goddess of Sorcery, Silver-footed Queen of the Night *~`~*</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(10/9/01 5:40:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Preference</span><hr size=1> Hades, I was curious, and I had pondered this while I was in the realm of the living. If you could, would you rather have Aphrodite or Hectate instead of me? <br>
<br>
I mean,  if Aprodite was more innocent. Because I overheard a couple of gods conversing, and they mentioned that every god wanted aphrodite for his own and...::looks fine but sounds as if she's about to cry:: and well, I know I don't even compare at all to Aphrodite's looks and character...<br>
<br>
And Hectate seemed like she would be someone you'd prefere because, well as she says, your &quot;morbid&quot; which is something I won't even try to understand. B-but she's hateful and dark and seems more fitted for this place than me... And I have done a lot of complaining since I was bounded here and all.... <br>
